se, we create a merge commit\\n    // that duplicates some entries (which is harmless for append-only shards).\\n}\\n\\n// Get local branch (re-read after potential reconciliation)\\nlocalRef, err := repo.Reference(plumbing.NewBranchReferenceName(branchName), true)\\n```\\n\\nThe rest of the function remains unchanged. After reconciliation, the local branch ref now sits on top of the remote tip (linear history). When we read it and compare trees, we'll find either:\\n- **Identical trees** (if reconciliation made local = remote): the merge is a no-op, but the function will still create a merge commit. This is harmless.\\n- **Local has additional data** (cherry-picked on top of remote): the tree merge will combine both, creating a valid merge commit.\\n\\n**Edge case -- reconciliation already happened:** If `ReconcileDisconnectedMetadataBranch` finds no disconnection (shared ancestry or same hash), it returns nil immediately. The fetch-and-merge continues as before, handling normal divergence via its tree-merge logic.\\n\\n**Edge case -- reconciliation fails:** We log a warning and continue. The tree merge in `fetchAndMergeSessionsCommon` will still attempt to combine entries from both trees. Since both trees contain unique shard paths, this produces a valid merged tree even without reconciliation. The result will be a merge commit with two unrelated parents (the disconnected branches), which is technically valid git but not ideal. On the next push cycle, the same reconciliation attempt will occur.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Part 6: Integrate detection and fix into `entire doctor`\\n\\n**File:** `/Users/dvydra/src/cli/cmd/entire/cli/doctor.go`\\n\\nThe doctor command needs to be broadened from \\\"Fix stuck sessions\\\" to a more general diagnostic tool. The disconnected metadata check should run **before** the stuck sessions check, since it affects a different subsystem.\\n\\n#### 6a. Update command metadata\\n\\nChange `Short` from `\\\"Fix stuck sessions\\\"` to `\\\"Diagnose and fix session issues\\\"`.\\n\\nUpdate `Long` to add a section about disconnected metadata branches:\\n\\n```\\nScan for session issues and offer to fix them.\\n\\nChecks performed:\\n  1. Disconnected metadata branches: local and remote entire/checkpoints/v1\\n     share no common ancestor (caused by a previous bug). Fixes by cherry-picking\\n     local checkpoints onto remote tip.\\n  2. Stuck sessions: sessions stuck in ACTIVE or ENDED phase that need cleanup.\\n\\nFor stuck sessions, you can choose to:\\n  - Condense: Save session data to permanent storage\\n  - Discard: Remove the session state and shadow branch data\\n  - Skip: Leave the session as-is\\n\\nUse --force to auto-fix all issues without prompting.\\n```\\n\\n#### 6b. Add disconnected metadata check\\n\\nAdd a new function `checkDisconnectedMetadata` and call it at the top of `runSessionsFix` (or rename the function to `runDoctor`).\\n\\n```go\\nfunc checkDisconnectedMetadata(cmd *cobra.Command, force bool) error {\\n    ctx := cmd.Context()\\n    repo, err := openRepository(ctx)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to open repository: %w\\\", err)\\n    }\\n\\n    disconnected, err := strategy.IsMetadataDisconnected(repo)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        fmt.Fprintf(cmd.ErrOrStderr(), \\\"Warning: could not check metadata branch state: %v\\\\n\\\", err)\\n        return nil // Non-fatal, continue to other checks\\n    }\\n\\n    if !disconnected {\\n        fmt.Fprintln(cmd.OutOrStdout(), \\\"Metadata branches: OK\\\")\\n        return nil\\n    }\\n\\n    fmt.Fprintln(cmd.OutOrStdout(), \\\"Metadata branches: DISCONNECTED\\\")\\n    fmt.Fprintln(cmd.OutOrStdout(), \\\"  Local and remote entire/checkpoints/v1 branches share no common ancestor.\\\")\\n    fmt.Fprintln(cmd.OutOrStdout(), \\\"  This was caused by a previous bug and means some remote checkpoints may not be visible.\\\")\\n    fmt.Fprintln(cmd.OutOrStdout(), \\\"  Fix: cherry-pick local checkpoints onto remote tip (preserves all data).\\\")\\n\\n    if !force {\\n        var confirmed bool\\n        form := NewAccessibleForm(\\n            huh.NewGroup(\\n                huh.NewConfirm().\\n                    Title(\\\"Fix disconnected metadata branches?\\\").\\n                    Value(&confirmed),\\n            ),\\n        )\\n        if err := form.Run(); err != nil {\\n            if errors.Is(err, huh.ErrUserAborted) {\\n                return nil\\n            }\\n            return fmt.Errorf(\\\"prompt failed: %w\\\", err)\\n        }\\n        if !confirmed {\\n            fmt.Fprintln(cmd.OutOrStdout(), \\\"  -> Skipped\\\")\\n            return nil\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    if err := strategy.ReconcileDisconnectedMetadataBranch(repo); err != nil {\\n        return fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to reconcile metadata branches: %w\\\", err)\\n    }\\n\\n    fmt.Fprintln(cmd.OutOrStdout(), \\\"  -> Fixed: metadata branches reconciled\\\")\\n    return nil\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThen in `runSessionsFix` (or renamed `runDoctor`), call it first:\\n\\n```go\\nfunc runSessionsFix(cmd *cobra.Command, force bool) error {\\n    // Check 1: Disconnected metadata branches\\n    if err := checkDisconnectedMetadata(cmd, force); err != nil {\\n        fmt.Fprintf(cmd.ErrOrStderr(), \\\"Warning: metadata check failed: %v\\\\n\\\", err)\\n        // Continue to other checks\\n    }\\n    fmt.Fprintln(cmd.OutOrStdout()) // blank line between sections\\n\\n    // Check 2: Stuck sessions (existing logic)\\n    ctx := cmd.Context()\\n    states, err := strategy.ListSessionStates(ctx)\\n    // ... rest of existing code ...\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Design decision: separate check vs integrated flow.** The disconnected metadata check is conceptually separate from stuck sessions. It involves different data (the metadata branch refs) and a different fix mechanism (cherry-pick vs condense/discard). Keeping it as a separate function called first is cleaner than trying to integrate it into the session iteration loop.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Part 7: Update comment in `EnsureMetadataBranch`\\n\\n**File:** `/Users/dvydra/src/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go` (around line 342)\\n\\nReplace:\\n```go\\n// Local has real data and differs from remote — reconciliation\\n// is handled by EnsureMetadataReconciled at read/write time\\n```\\n\\nWith:\\n```go\\n// Local has real data and differs from remote — if disconnected\\n// (no common ancestor), reconciliation happens at pre-push time\\n// or via 'entire doctor'. Read paths warn but do not auto-fix.\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Part 8: Update tests\\n\\n**File:** `/Users/dvydra/src/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/metadata_reconcile_test.go`\\n\\nAdd tests for the new `IsMetadataDisconnected()` function. These can largely mirror the existing tests but verify the boolean return instead of side effects:\\n\\n1. `TestIsMetadataDisconnected_NoRemote` -- returns `(false, nil)`\\n2. `TestIsMetadataDisconnected_NoLocal` -- returns `(false, nil)`\\n3. `TestIsMetadataDisconnected_SameHash` -- returns `(false, nil)`\\n4. `TestIsMetadataDisconnected_SharedAncestry` -- returns `(false, nil)`\\n5. `TestIsMetadataDisconnected_Disconnected` -- returns `(true, nil)`\\n\\nThese can reuse the existing `initBareWithMetadataBranch` and `cloneWithConfig` helpers from `common_test.go`.\\n\\n**File:** A new test or addition to existing doctor tests for the disconnected metadata check in `entire doctor`. This would likely be an integration test since it needs a real git repo with disconnected branches.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Implementation Sequence\\n\\n1. **Add `IsMetadataDisconnected()` and `WarnIfMetadataDisconnected()`** to `metadata_reconcile.go`. These are new functions with no callers yet, so nothing breaks.\\n\\n2. **Add tests** for `IsMetadataDisconnected()` in `metadata_reconcile_test.go`.\\n\\n3. **Replace the 3 call sites** that use `EnsureMetadataReconciled()`:\\n   - `ListCheckpoints()` in `common.go` line 148\\n   - `getCheckpointStore()` in `manual_commit.go` line 55\\n   - `getBranchCheckpoints()` in `explain.go` line 897\\n   \\n   Each becomes `WarnIfMetadataDisconnected()`.\\n\\n4. **Remove `EnsureMetadataReconciled()`** and its globals from `common.go` lines 49-69.\\n\\n5. **Add reconciliation to `fetchAndMergeSessionsCommon()`** in `push_common.go`, between the repo open and local ref read.\\n\\n6. **Update `entire doctor`** in `doctor.go` with the disconnected metadata check.\\n\\n7. **Update the comment** in `EnsureMetadataBranch` at `common.go` line 342.\\n\\n8. **Run `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`** to validate.\\n\\nSteps 1-2 can be done together. Steps 3-4 should be done together (removing the old function and updating all callers atomically). Steps 5, 6, and 7 are independent of each other and can be done in any order after steps 3-4.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Potential Challenges\\n\\n1. **Race between warning and push:** A user might see the warning from a read path, then immediately push. The push will reconcile, clearing the issue. The warning is harmless in this case -- it just looks slightly redundant. Since the warning uses `sync.Once`, the user sees it at most once per process anyway.\\n\\n2. **Reconciliation during push timeout:** The `fetchAndMergeSessionsCommon` function already has a 2-minute timeout context. The `ReconcileDisconnectedMetadataBranch` call within it will be bounded by this same timeout. The internal `isDisconnected` call has its own 10-second timeout for the `git merge-base` subprocess. This is fine.\\n\\n3. **Doctor opening repo twice:** The `checkDisconnectedMetadata` function opens the repo, and so does the stuck sessions check later. This is consistent with the existing pattern in doctor.go (line 77 already opens the repo). Each open is lightweight (just finding `.git`). If desired, the repo could be opened once and passed through, but that would require restructuring the function signatures, which is unnecessary churn.\\n\\n4. **`getCheckpointStore` sync.Once caching:** The `getCheckpointStore` method uses `sync.Once`, so the `WarnIfMetadataDisconnected()` call inside it only runs on first initialization. This is the desired behavior -- we warn once per process. However, if reconciliation happens later (during push), the checkpoint store still points to the pre-reconciliation repo state. Since `checkpoint.GitStore` wraps a `*git.Repository`, and ref lookups go through the repo's storer (which reads live refs from disk), the store will automatically see updated refs after reconciliation. No stale data issue.\\n\\n5. **Renaming `runSessionsFix`:** The function name is internal, but renaming it to `runDoctor` would better reflect its broadened scope. This is optional polish.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Critical Files for Implementation\\n\\n- `/Users/dvydra/src/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/metadata_reconcile.go` - Add `IsMetadataDisconnected()` and `WarnIfMetadataDisconnected()` functions\\n- `/Users/dvydra/src/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go` - Remove `EnsureMetadataReconciled()`, update `ListCheckpoints()` call site, update `EnsureMetadataBranch` comment\\n- `/Users/dvydra/src/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/push_common.go` - Insert reconciliation into `fetchAndMergeSessionsCommon()` after fetch, before local ref read\\n- `/Users/dvydra/src/cli/cmd/entire/cli/doctor.go` - Add disconnected metadata detection/fix check, broaden command description\\n- `/Users/dvydra/src/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit.go` - Replace `EnsureMetadataReconciled()` with `WarnIfMetadataDisconnected()` in `getCheckpointStore()`\"}],\"totalDurationMs\":195296,\"totalTokens\":82418,\"totalToolUseCount\":36,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1578,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":75114,\"output_tokens\":5725,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1578,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"