s become disconnected (no common ancestor). Currently, reconciliation is called eagerly from 3 read paths via `EnsureMetadataReconciled()`. This is too aggressive — reconciliation should only happen at well-defined fix points, not on every checkpoint read.\\n\\n**New approach:** Only reconcile in pre-push (before tree merge) and `entire doctor`. All other read paths just detect + warn, pointing users to `entire doctor`.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. Add `IsMetadataDisconnected()` and `WarnIfMetadataDisconnected()`\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/metadata_reconcile.go`\\n\\n- **`IsMetadataDisconnected(repo *git.Repository) (bool, error)`** — lightweight detection-only function. Looks up local/remote refs, compares hashes, calls existing `isDisconnected()`. Returns `(true, nil)` only when truly disconnected.\\n- **`WarnIfMetadataDisconnected()`** — `sync.Once` wrapper that opens repo, calls `IsMetadataDisconnected`, and prints a one-time stderr warning: \\\"Local and remote session metadata branches are disconnected. Some checkpoints from remote may not be visible. Run 'entire doctor' to fix.\\\"\\n- New globals: `disconnectedOnce sync.Once`, `disconnectedResult bool` (replacing the old `reconcileOnce`/`reconcileResult`)\\n\\n### 2. Remove `EnsureMetadataReconciled()` and replace call sites\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go`\\n- Delete `reconcileOnce`, `reconcileResult` globals (lines 51-54)\\n- Delete `EnsureMetadataReconciled()` function (lines 56-69)\\n- In `ListCheckpoints()` (line 148): replace `EnsureMetadataReconciled()` call with `WarnIfMetadataDisconnected()`\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit.go`\\n- In `getCheckpointStore()` (line 55): replace `EnsureMetadataReconciled()` call with `WarnIfMetadataDisconnected()`\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/explain.go`\\n- In `getBranchCheckpoints()` (line 897): replace `strategy.EnsureMetadataReconciled()` call with `strategy.WarnIfMetadataDisconnected()`\\n\\n### 3. Add reconciliation to pre-push flow\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/push_common.go`\\n\\nIn `fetchAndMergeSessionsCommon()`, insert reconciliation **after** the fetch (line 136, so remote-tracking ref is fresh) and **after** `OpenRepository` (line 138), but **before** reading the local ref (line 144):\\n\\n```go\\n// After repo open, before reading local ref:\\nif reconcileErr := ReconcileDisconnectedMetadataBranch(repo); reconcileErr != nil {\\n    fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \\\"[entire] Warning: metadata reconciliation failed: %v\\\\n\\\", reconcileErr)\\n}\\n\\n// Now read local ref (may have been updated by reconciliation)\\nlocalRef, err := repo.Reference(...)\\n```\\n\\nAfter reconciliation, local branch is ahead of remote (linear), so the tree merge creates a valid (if slightly redundant) merge commit. The subsequent push succeeds.\\n\\n### 4. Add disconnected metadata check to `entire doctor`\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/doctor.go`\\n\\n- Update `Short` to `\\\"Diagnose and fix session issues\\\"`\\n- Update `Long` to describe both checks (disconnected metadata + stuck sessions)\\n- Add `checkDisconnectedMetadata(cmd, force)` function that:\\n  1. Opens repo, calls `strategy.IsMetadataDisconnected(repo)`\\n  2. If not disconnected: prints \\\"Metadata branches: OK\\\"\\n  3. If disconnected: explains the situation, prompts for confirmation (or auto-fixes with `--force`)\\n  4. Calls `strategy.ReconcileDisconnectedMetadataBranch(repo)` to fix\\n- Call it at the top of `runSessionsFix` before the stuck sessions check\\n- Uses `NewAccessibleForm` + `huh.NewConfirm` for the interactive prompt (consistent with existing doctor pattern)\\n\\n### 5. Update `EnsureMetadataBranch` comment\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go` (line 341-342)\\n\\nReplace:\\n```go\\n// is handled by EnsureMetadataReconciled at read/write time\\n```\\nWith:\\n```go\\n// is reconciled at pre-push time or via 'entire doctor'\\n```\\n\\n### 6. Tests\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/stra