e situation, prompts for confirmation (or auto-fixes with `--force`)\\n  4. Calls `strategy.ReconcileDisconnectedMetadataBranch(repo)` to fix\\n- Call it at the top of `runSessionsFix` before the stuck sessions check\\n- Uses `NewAccessibleForm` + `huh.NewConfirm` for the interactive prompt (consistent with existing doctor pattern)\\n\\n### 5. Update `EnsureMetadataBranch` comment\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go` (line 341-342)\\n\\nReplace:\\n```go\\n// is handled by EnsureMetadataReconciled at read/write time\\n```\\nWith:\\n```go\\n// is reconciled at pre-push time or via 'entire doctor'\\n```\\n\\n### 6. Tests\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/metadata_reconcile_test.go`\\n- Add tests for `IsMetadataDisconnected()` covering: no remote, no local, same hash, shared ancestry (returns false), disconnected (returns true)\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/doctor_test.go`\\n- Add test for the disconnected metadata doctor check (if feasible with existing test infrastructure)\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n2. Manually verify: create a repo with disconnected metadata branches, confirm:\\n   - Read paths (explain, rewind list) show the warning once\\n   - `entire doctor` detects and offers to fix\\n   - Pre-push reconciles before tree merge\\n\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_019BL6S1c8EFFGzweKZyXJ1p\"}]},\"uuid\":\"ff6d4205-ea4e-4471-9ab0-3f71f98c62e5\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T04:05:25.547Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"plan\":\"# Refactor: Move metadata reconciliation to pre-push and doctor only\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe PR adds `ReconcileDisconnectedMetadataBranch()` to fix a bug where local and remote `entire/checkpoints/v1` branches become disconnected (no common ancestor). Currently, reconciliation is called eagerly from 3 read paths via `EnsureMetadataReconciled()`. This is too aggressive — reconciliation should only happen at well-defined fix points, not on every checkpoint read.\\n\\n**New approach:** On